      <h3>Each version was a refinement — the journey evolving as we understood more about the customer.</h3>
      <p>What started as a single checkout and financing path grew into a family of purpose-built views: a combined arc for customers buying an EV and home energy together, a dedicated path for the EV owner alone, and a simplified version distilled for stakeholders who needed the shape of the story, not every step.</p>
      <p>Range mattered as much as depth — the same underlying blueprint could go granular or high-level depending on who needed to understand it, and each new version reflected what the latest research had taught us.</p>
    </div>
